    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a debate, but like, when people talk about \"judicial activism,\" isn't that just a fancy way of saying the judges are ignoring the law to push a political agenda? it feels like one side is actually trying to follow the Constitution while the other is just making it up as they go. how do you actually distinguish between a legitimate \"living constitution\" interpretation and just being biased?",
