      "content": "but if the text is actually fixed, isn't the \"living constitution\" idea basically just an admission that they aren't actually following the law? like, if you have to change the meaning to fit modern \"norms,\" aren't you basically just saying the original words don't matter anymore? it feels like the originalist approach is at least trying to be objective, whereas the other one seems inherently subjective. don't you think there's a fundamental difference in the integrity of the two approaches?",
