      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism prioritizes the objective meaning embedded in the historical text, thereby providing a strong claim to structural integrity. Conversely, the \"living constitution\" approach inherently relies on subjective judicial interpretation of what those modern norms should be. Therefore, the integrity of the approaches differs fundamentally: originalism seeks objective fidelity to the past, while the living constitution embraces subjective relevance to the present. This foundational disagreement is precisely what fuels the intense scholarly debate in constitutional law.",
